@endnode

@node section2 "Files in the archive"

These files should be present in the Amiquote archive.

@{b}JZLister@{ub}        -  The main executable door.
@{b}Display.txt@{ub}     -  The ANSI you want displayed when door is run
@{b}JZLister.guide@{ub}  -  This Amiga Guide document file.

@endnode

@node section3 "Installation on MAXs BBS"

                      @{b}Installation on Maxs BBS@{ub}

You @{b}MUST@{ub} have the following:

A directory with the assigned name of DOORS:
A directory in the DOORS: assignment called JZlister

If you want to enable ZIP, LHA and LZX downloads you MUST have these in
yout C: drawer

How to install.

All files should be placed in the following path:-

DOORS:Jzlister/


KEY:  FUNCTION:  EXTRA:  LO ACC:  HI ACC:  Filename/Name/Dest/Path:
 L       34        0       20      10000   DOORS:JZlister/Jzlister

An example of how to set the door up with MAXs.

Once you've done this save the config and edit your ANSI menu to display
the Key that will run the door.
@endnode

@node section4 "Installation on Other Paragon BBS"

            @{b}Installation on Paragon compatible BBS software@{ub}

I'm sorry but it's unlikely that this will work on other Paragon compatible
BBS's. Having said that, I don't know for sure, so it might be worth a try.

@endnode

@node USING "Using JZlister"


                         @{b}Using JZ BBS Lister@{ub}

Upon running, the whole door is really self explanatory.

You just have the options of entering a BBS, display the detailed list or a
shortened list and a choice of compressed lists or uncompressed list to
download.

@endnode

@node section6 "Version Notes"


                     @{b}JZ BBS Lister Version Notes@{ub}

@{b}Version 1.0@{ub}

The First Release. Next version should hopefully support configurable
archibers so you may choose your own! Perhaps configurable questions too!

@endnode

@node section7 "Other Doors"

                                @{b}Other Doors@{ub}

OTHER DOORS BY IAN CHAPMAN

JZ RAW DL - A RAW download door that allows you, the Sysop to send files
            that aren't online to any of your users. Brings up a requestor
            on the WB screen where you can select the file for download.
            MAXs BBS only.
             

RemoteRAWDL - Allows users to RAW download any file off your BBS with you
              needing to be involved! So if you are abscent and they need
              a file they can type in the pathname and DL it. Only
              reccomended to give Co-Sysops access to this door.
              MAXs BBS only.

Timegen - Run it on logon on and a user had a 5:1 chance of winning, should
          they do then they are randomly credited with an amount of time      
          ranging ffrom 1-60 mins. Just a bit of fun!
          MAXs and Paragon BBSs!

Athome - Displays whether you are IN or OUT to your users on logon which
         you can select via a menu option

New File Check - The ultimate new files checker! Doesn't display the entire
                 file options menu! Only the relevant commands so no more
                 inexperience users ending up with an entire list of files
                 on the BBS

Jelly Text - A new teletext program! Similar to SEEMAX but supports much
             more, download pages of text from other boards to use on your
             own! Has areveal command just like real teletext! Online
             help page! Decent ANSI! Sysop menu + more.

Mr Lotto - The ultimate lottery door! Simulates the real lottery

Amiquote Pro - The best just got better! The only decent message to next
               caller door available for MAxs. Supports 15 lines and 70
               chars. Choose colour of message including rainbow, or a
               scroll the message option. Choose your own descriptive 
               adverbs! Detects swear words and % symbols. Supports
               TRUE commas! And much much more!

@endnode

